typeDescription: Model information for a cell line that is derived from a mammalian organism.

fields.name: Name
fields.description: Name of this Object.

fields.name: ID
fields.description: ID of this Object.

fields.name: Object
fields.description: Object of this Object.

metadata.value: The object reference of this object.

fields.name: Type
fields.description: Type of this Object.

fields.name: Notebook
fields.description: Notebook this object belongs to.

fields.name: Synonyms
fields.description: List of possible alternative names this model goes by.

fields.name: Authors
fields.description: The people who created this model.

fields.name: ATCCID
fields.description: The American Type Culture Collection (ATCC) identifying number of this cell line.

fields.name: Species
fields.description: The species that this cell was originally cultivated from.

fields.name: Viruses
fields.description: Viruses that are known to be carried by this cell line.

fields.name: cDNAs
fields.description: The cDNA models that this cell line produces.

fields.name: Transcripts
fields.description: The transcript models that this cell line produces.

fields.name: Lysates
fields.description: The model of the contents of this cell when lysed.

fields.name: Tissues
fields.description: The types of tissue that this cell helps comprise.

fields.name: DefaultSampleModel
fields.description: Specifies the model of sample that will be used if this model is specified to be used in an experiment.

fields.name: Diameter
fields.description: The average diameter of an individual cell.

fields.name: DoublingTime
fields.description: The average period of time it takes for a population of these cells to double in number during their exponential growth phase in its preferred media.

fields.name: DetectionLabels
fields.description: Indicate the tags (e.g. GFP, Alexa Fluor 488) that the cell contains, which can indicate the presence and amount of particular features or molecules in the cell.

fields.name: CellType
fields.description: The primary types of cells that are contained within this sample.

fields.name: pH
fields.description: The logarithmic concentration of hydrogen ions of a pure sample of this molecule at room temperature and pressure.

fields.name: Morphology
fields.description: The morphological type of the cell line.

fields.name: IncubationTemperature
fields.description: The nominal incubation temperature at which this cell line grows.

fields.name: PreferredLiquidMedia
fields.description: The recommended liquid media for the growth of the cells.

fields.name: PreferredSolidMedia
fields.description: The recommended solid media for the growth of the cells.

fields.name: PreferredFreezingMedia
fields.description: The recommended media for cryopreservation of these cells, often containing additives that protect the cells during freezing.

fields.name: CultureAdhesion
fields.description: The default type of cell culture (adherent or suspension) that should be performed when growing these cells. If a cell line can be cultured via an adherent or suspension culture, this is set to the most common cell culture type for the cell line.

fields.name: ThawCellsMethod
fields.description: The default method by which to thaw cryovials of this cell line.

fields.name: WashCellsMethod
fields.description: The default method by which to wash cultures of this cell line.

fields.name: ChangeMediaMethod
fields.description: The default method by which to change the media for cultures of this cell line.

fields.name: SplitCellsMethod
fields.description: The default method by which to split this cell line.

fields.name: Radioactive
fields.description: Indicates if this molecule emits substantial ionizing radiation.

fields.name: Ventilated
fields.description: Indicates if a pure sample of this molecule must be handled in a ventilated enclosures.

fields.name: Flammable
fields.description: Indicates if a pure sample of this molecule is easily set aflame at room temperature and pressure.

fields.name: Acid
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule are strong acids (pH <= 2).

fields.name: Base
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule are strong acids (pH >= 12).

fields.name: Pyrophoric
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule can ignite spontaneously upon exposure to air.

fields.name: WaterReactive
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule react spontaneously upon exposure to water.

fields.name: Fuming
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule emit fumes spontaneously when exposed to air.

fields.name: HazardousBan
fields.description: Indicates this molecule is currently banned from usage in the ECL because the facility isn't yet equiped to handle it.

fields.name: ExpirationHazard
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule become hazardous once they are expired and must be automatically disposed of when they pass their expiration date.

fields.name:
ParticularlyHazardous
Substance
fields.description: Indicates if special precautions should be taken in handling this molecule, as indicated by the MSDS classification.

fields.name: DrainDisposal
fields.description: Indicates if this molecule may be safely disposed down a standard drain.

fields.name: Pungent
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule have a strong odor.

fields.name: MSDSRequired
fields.description: Indicates if an MSDS is required for this molecule.

fields.name: MSDSFile
fields.description: The PDF of the MSDS (Materials Saftey Data Sheet) of this molecule.

fields.name: NFPA
fields.description: The National Fire Protection Association (NFPA) 704 hazard diamond classification for this molecule.

fields.name: DOTHazardClass
fields.description: The Department of Transportation hazard classification for this molecule.

fields.name: BiosafetyLevel
fields.description: The Biosafety classification for this molecule.

fields.name: LightSensitive
fields.description: Indicates if this molecule reacts or degrades in the presence of light.

fields.name: IncompatibleMaterials
fields.description: A list of materials that would be damaged if wetted by this molecule.

fields.name: LiquidHandlerIncompatible
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule cannot be reliably aspirated or dispensed on an automated liquid handling robot.

fields.name: PipettingMethod
fields.description: The pipetting parameters used to manipulate pure samples of this model.

fields.name: UltrasonicIncompatible
fields.description: Indicates if pure samples of this molecule cannot be performed via the ultrasonic distance method due to vapors interfering with the reading.

fields.name: ReferenceImages
fields.description: Reference microscope images exemplifying the typical appearance of this cell line.

fields.name: GrowthCurves
fields.description:
The standard curve used to convert turbidity measurements to cell counts.
							The cell count conversion factor is the slope of the standard curve, which is used to convert turbidity measurements to cell count.

fields.name: GrowthCurveAcquisition
fields.description:
A description of the acquisition parameters used to collect the data to create the GrowthCurve.
							The method indicates whether the data was collected by absorbance or nephelometry.
							The instrument model indicates the model of the instrument used to collect the standard curve data.
							If the method used was Nephelometry, the beam aperture indicates the diameter of the opening allowing the source light to pass through to the sample when the data was collected.
							If the method used was Nephelometry, the beam intensity indicates the percentage of the total amount of the source light passed through to hit the sample when the data was collected.
							If the method used was Nephelometry, integration time indicates the amount of time that light was measured to determine turbidity when the data was collected.
							If the method used was Absorbance, the wavelength indicates the wavelength of light at which the measurements were taken.
